==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[gaufrer]] ‘stamp with patterned tool’, from [[gaufre]] ‘honeycomb’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'gɒfə/

===Verb===
'''goffer'''
# to make [[wavy]], to [[crimp]]
#:*'''1985''': On the back of a chair beside the bed sits perched above the discarded chip hat something apparently precious and taken from the opened bundle on the floor: a flat white cambric hat, its fronts and sides '''goffered''' into little flutes — John Fowles, ''A Maggot''